              Covariances, BNL, July, 2011                        4225 1451
New set of covariances was obtained at BNL in 2010 using kernel   4225 1451
approach in the resonance region and EMPIRE/KALMAN analysis of    4225 1451
experimental data in the fast neutron region.                     4225 1451
                                                                  4225 1451
Dispersion analysis of the evaluated libraries was not very       4225 1451
helpful since all major libraries are virtually identical.        4225 1451
ROSFOND disagrees somewhat, but only capture (15% above 10 MeV)   4225 1451
shows significant disagreement. Fairly complete isotopic          4225 1451
experimental data are available, but only a few points for        4225 1451
capture, thus elemental data were also used. In KALMAN            4225 1451
fitting, we used uncertainties of total and absorption            4225 1451
scaling factors to account for systematic uncertainties.          4225 1451
